args: ＂In business, you're in the way. Just don't.＂
Okay, are you TRYING to sabotage\nme here, Elisanne?!
Of course not!! The hallway was merely\ncluttered, so I thought to help by tidying it.
Do you have ANY idea how long it took me\nto sort all that product?! And now it's all\nruined! Broken! DESTROYED!
I'm terribly sorry, truly. But you see,\nMatilda suddenly appeared at my feet,\nso I—

I'm sorry. MATILDA? You expect me to
buy that a stuffed animal just showed up
out of nowhere? I've heard lame excuses
before, but that is LAMER than lame.
But it is the truth! She simply appeared\nbefore me as if from thin air!
Well, you can stick with whatever stupid\nstory you want, but I still expect you to\nhelp me sort this mess out!
Say, so I don't wanna pry or nothing...\nBUT WHY ARE YOU ON FIRE?!
Well, that's one way to put a fire out.\nFeeling better there? ...Elisanne?
Huh. I'm no water scientist, but I\nreally think she should have come\nup for air by now...
Oh, hell! Hang on, Elisanne! I'm comin'!
*GASP* *HEAVE* I forgot...I was wearing\na kimono... *COUGH* I thought that would\nbe the end of me for certain.
Well, I'm very glad it wasn't—and also,\nI am so, so, SO sorry about that whole\n＂setting you on fire＂ thing.
I never thought for a second the flame\nfrom that teeeeeny little explosion would\ncatch your ponytail like that.
Explosion? Wait, I thought you two were\ndoing the rounds offering New Year's\ngreetings. What exploded?
Luca, have you MET Sinoa?\nEverything explodes around her.
You needn't be. I expected something like\nthis to happen the moment I saw we had\nbeen paired up.
＂Your wish will be foiled by another's\ninterference. Too bad, so sad!＂

Oof! Between helping Francesca and the
New Year's greeting debacle—not to
mention my patrols and training—I am
simply exhausted.
I need a moment of rest. Only a moment...
*sigh* It seems there is no rest for\nthe brave and resourceful this day...
You have it so good as an animal, Matilda.\nNo work is piled high upon your plate,\nand no one takes you to task for errors.
I wish I could be an animal, too—or nay,\na plant! Plants simply exist as the world \nrushes by all around them.
They don't have to walk, or talk, or...\nPffft! Aaah ha ha ha!
By the Goddess, even the vegetables\naren't afforded a moment's rest here.
I just...wanted a little break...\nJust a short rest... And yet... Nnngh...
Are you all right, Elly? I heard you fainted.
I apologize for causing a scene, Highness.\nI was able to rest for a while after that,\nso you needn't worry over me.
With everything on that omikuji coming\ntrue, I'd be worn out, too.
You see I... Hmm? This presence...
Er, ain't that your stuffy buddy?
Aw, Matilda is adorable!\nThere's no need to be scared of—
She's always there. SHE'S ALWAYS THERE!
At the scene of the crime when the\neffects of the omikuji come to pass!
I haven't once taken her out of my room,\nbut she's always there! It is as if she is\nwatching me! FOLLOWING me!
The omikuji said I'm ＂bunlucky＂!\nTHAT is what this is!
Let's all maybe take a deep breath or five,\nyeah? I don't think Matilda is stalking you.
I'm bunlucky because of Matilda!\nIT'S MATILDA BECAUSE I'M BUNLUCKY!
Plus, even if everything written on that\nomikuji IS gonna come true, so what?
I mean, you've been through nearly\nall of it by now, right?
Now that you mention it, the only entries\nstill untouched are the person I await and\nmy romantic fortunes...
＂The one you await isn't coming,\nso go seek them out yourself.＂
And ＂In love, you're unstoppable—and the\none you fancy will sit up and take notice.\nGo get 'im, snuggle bunny!＂
(Neither sound TOO terrible, but it is hard\nto say what effects they might bring...)
You know, maybe it makes sense to just\nget those two over with so you can go back\nto your normal, boring, Elisanne life.
